WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:03.668
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da,
ba-da-ba-da-ba ♪

00:03.703 --> 00:05.170
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da ♪
Let's go!

00:05.205 --> 00:06.872
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:06.907 --> 00:09.541
♪ A wink and a smile
and a great old time ♪

00:09.576 --> 00:11.743
♪ Yeah, we'll be there ♪

00:11.778 --> 00:13.845
♪ Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found ♪

00:13.880 --> 00:16.181
♪ We'll be there
when you turn that corner ♪

00:16.216 --> 00:17.516
♪ We'll jump out the bush ♪

00:17.551 --> 00:19.217
♪ With a big bear hug
and a smile ♪

00:19.252 --> 00:20.686
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:27.928 --> 00:29.027
[ Laughs ]

00:29.062 --> 00:30.162
Oh, yeah.

00:30.197 --> 00:31.696
Time to get comfy.

00:31.731 --> 00:32.697
Ooh. [ Sighs ]

00:32.732 --> 00:35.033
Hurry, guys!
It's starting soon!

00:35.068 --> 00:36.234
Yeah, coming!

00:36.269 --> 00:37.436
Whoa-uh-uh!

00:37.471 --> 00:40.872
[ Vacuum whirring ]

00:40.907 --> 00:42.340
Ice Bear
ready for drama.

00:42.375 --> 00:43.942
[<i> Screeches</i> ]

00:43.977 --> 00:46.211
♪♪

00:46.246 --> 00:47.846
Hey, Charlie.
Hurry.

00:47.881 --> 00:49.047
It just got started.

00:49.082 --> 00:50.682
Coming, fellas.
Sorry about that.

00:50.717 --> 00:53.251
Had to pull my cheesy poof
casserole from the oven.

00:53.286 --> 00:55.620
Oh! Why, Pan Man,
you don't have a snack.

00:55.655 --> 00:57.689
Here. Some chips
for my best bud.

00:57.724 --> 00:59.958
I've got plain, barbecue,
sour cream and onion.

00:59.993 --> 01:01.359
Blech! Ugh!

01:01.394 --> 01:03.228
Dude, gross!
I don't want your feet-chips!

01:03.263 --> 01:04.229
Just have a seat.

01:04.264 --> 01:05.230
Ah, with pleasure.

01:05.265 --> 01:06.431
-[ Groans ]
-Mwah!

01:06.466 --> 01:08.100
Oh, you got to try
this casserole.

01:08.135 --> 01:09.101
It's ice cold.

01:09.136 --> 01:10.368
Come on, man!
Remember?

01:10.403 --> 01:12.070
-Personal space!
-Shh! Shh!

01:12.105 --> 01:15.574
<i>So you have deceived me.</i>
<i>You are no heir to the throne.</i>

01:15.609 --> 01:17.242
<i>I was a fool</i>
<i>to have loved you.</i>

01:17.277 --> 01:18.643
Now remind me again,
Pan Man,

01:18.678 --> 01:20.912
which one is Mr. Swords
and which one is Mr. Castles?

01:20.947 --> 01:23.281
They're not all named
Swords and Castles, Charlie.

01:23.316 --> 01:24.983
[ Static hisses ]
Huh?

01:25.018 --> 01:26.918
W-What? No!
What's going on?!

01:26.953 --> 01:29.221
Ooh, this is my favorite show
right here!

01:29.256 --> 01:30.822
This is not a show,
Charlie.

01:30.857 --> 01:31.923
Course, it is.

01:31.958 --> 01:34.426
My favorite part's
when it goes [hissing]

01:34.461 --> 01:35.427
[ Television turns off ]

01:35.462 --> 01:36.761
Ah, gosh dang it,

01:36.796 --> 01:38.396
The satellite dish
must be down again.

01:38.431 --> 01:40.132
Ice Bear disappointed.
The spell is broken.

01:40.167 --> 01:41.466
Wait,
are you guys talking

01:41.501 --> 01:43.568
about that big old
salad bowl on your roof?

01:43.603 --> 01:45.070
Let me go fiddle
with it.

01:45.105 --> 01:46.438
Uh, I don't know,
Charlie.

01:46.473 --> 01:47.472
Maybe we should
call someone?

01:47.507 --> 01:49.107
Eh, let him try, guys.

01:49.142 --> 01:51.576
Maybe Charlie can actually
help us fix something for once.

01:51.611 --> 01:54.112
You bet I can, Pan Man!
I'll make you proud!

01:54.147 --> 01:55.780
Wait, uh,
Charlie, maybe --

01:55.815 --> 01:57.115
And there he goes.

01:57.150 --> 01:59.751
Don't you worry, guys.
I'll have this fixed in no time.

01:59.786 --> 02:00.819
[ Sighs ]

02:00.854 --> 02:03.021
Okay, uh, where --
where is it, again?

02:03.056 --> 02:04.256
Aha!

02:04.291 --> 02:05.957
Okay, just give this
a little twist.

02:05.992 --> 02:07.325
[ Laughing ]

02:07.360 --> 02:10.996
[ Clattering, screaming ]

02:11.031 --> 02:12.297
[ Thunk! ]
- Ow!

02:12.332 --> 02:13.932
[ All gasp ]

02:13.967 --> 02:16.268
Charlie, are you okay?

02:16.303 --> 02:17.636
Oh, yeah, guys.
I'm fine.

02:17.671 --> 02:19.471
Let's go put
this thing back up.

02:19.506 --> 02:21.306
Oh, my gosh!
Charlie, your foot!

02:21.341 --> 02:23.308
Your -- Your
hideous foot!

02:23.343 --> 02:24.976
Ah, nah,
don't worry about it.

02:25.011 --> 02:26.378
I break stuff
all the time.

02:26.413 --> 02:28.313
It always heals fine,
like my elbow.

02:28.348 --> 02:30.715
Bent it weird last week,
now it's good as new.

02:30.750 --> 02:33.218
[ Squeaking ]

02:33.253 --> 02:35.287
Yeah, Charlie, you can't
just brush this off.

02:35.322 --> 02:37.155
I think we should take you
to a doctor.

02:37.190 --> 02:38.323
Whoa! No way, amigos!

02:38.358 --> 02:39.824
You know how I feel
about people.

02:39.859 --> 02:40.825
Ow! Ah!

02:40.860 --> 02:43.161
Look at me.
I've never been better.

02:43.196 --> 02:44.829
See?
[ Chuckles ]

02:44.864 --> 02:45.997
Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!

02:46.032 --> 02:47.332
Whoa!

02:47.367 --> 02:48.533
Charlie, we've got to get you
to a hospital.

02:48.568 --> 02:50.335
Yeah, it does seem
kind of bad.

02:50.370 --> 02:52.304
Ice Bear thinks
amputation necessary.

02:52.339 --> 02:53.471
Ahh! No! No way!

02:53.506 --> 02:55.507
I ain't into that
one bit.

02:55.542 --> 02:57.475
You know what?
- I'll catch you guys later.

02:57.510 --> 02:59.411
We'll finish that show
another time. Bye!

02:59.446 --> 03:00.512
Wait, Charlie!

03:00.547 --> 03:01.846
Panda,
say something to him.

03:01.881 --> 03:04.015
He's your best bud.
He'll listen to you.

03:04.050 --> 03:05.383
What?
I'm not his best bud.

03:05.418 --> 03:06.885
[ Growling ]

03:06.920 --> 03:08.053
Ugh. Okay.

03:08.088 --> 03:09.521
Charlie, wait!

03:09.556 --> 03:11.089
As your best bud,

03:11.124 --> 03:13.758
I really think we should go
to the hospital.

03:13.793 --> 03:15.994
Please? Charlie?

03:16.029 --> 03:17.696
Um...uh...

03:17.731 --> 03:18.997
Uh...okay.

03:19.032 --> 03:21.333
But only if they just look
at my foot, not the rest of me.

03:21.368 --> 03:24.836
Wha-- How the heck
are we going to do that?

03:24.871 --> 03:26.772
Ice Bear has idea.

03:28.108 --> 03:30.442
Okay, Pan Pan, this is
definitely going to work.

03:30.477 --> 03:32.544
I don't know, guys.
Maybe we should just bail.

03:32.579 --> 03:33.678
-Don't worry.
-Hey!

03:33.713 --> 03:35.380
Stay put
and you'll be fine.

03:35.415 --> 03:37.716
Man, why do I have to be
the one doing this?

03:37.751 --> 03:39.918
'Cause, Panda,
he's your best friend.

03:39.953 --> 03:41.253
Sign.

03:41.288 --> 03:42.454
Charlie: Oh, yeah.

03:42.489 --> 03:44.623
Uh, uh, yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

03:48.261 --> 03:49.261
Charlie!

03:49.296 --> 03:50.562
Shh!
Don't blow my cover!

03:50.597 --> 03:51.863
Ooh!
I am nervous, boys.

03:51.898 --> 03:53.598
Well, if you weren't
such a klutz,

03:53.633 --> 03:55.567
we wouldn't be here
in the first place.

03:55.602 --> 03:57.035
Oh, I was just trying
to help.

03:57.070 --> 03:59.437
Both of you, calm down.
You've got to be one.

03:59.472 --> 04:01.139
[ Knock on door ]
[ Gasps ]

04:01.174 --> 04:02.274
[ Clears throat ]

04:02.309 --> 04:04.142
Hello.
How are you doing today?

04:04.177 --> 04:08.413
I'm Dr. Clark.
- Can I see your papers, please?

04:08.448 --> 04:09.447
So, Panda?

04:09.482 --> 04:10.649
That's me!

04:10.684 --> 04:12.717
Let's see.
Possible broken foot.

04:12.752 --> 04:15.153
Yep, and that's definitely
the only thing wrong here.

04:15.188 --> 04:16.588
Yeah, that might be true
and all,

04:16.623 --> 04:18.623
but I'm going to have to run
a few tests first.

04:18.658 --> 04:20.091
Standard stuff,
you know.

04:20.126 --> 04:21.226
Oh, um...

04:21.261 --> 04:23.428
I guess that --
that's fine.

04:23.463 --> 04:26.932
♪♪

04:30.470 --> 04:32.270
Mm-hmm.

04:32.305 --> 04:33.305
[ Grunts ]

04:33.340 --> 04:34.806
[ Chuckles ]

04:43.883 --> 04:46.084
[ Heartbeat ]

04:46.119 --> 04:47.485
[ Bass line playing ]

04:47.520 --> 04:49.021
[ Chuckles ]

04:56.996 --> 04:58.963
Charlie: Oh!

04:58.998 --> 05:00.499
Shh!

05:01.801 --> 05:03.034
Interesting.

05:03.069 --> 05:06.037
So is, uh,
everything good, Doc?

05:06.072 --> 05:10.141
It's okay, I guess.
Now let's see that foot.

05:10.176 --> 05:12.143
Hmm.

05:12.178 --> 05:13.144
[ Crunch! ]

05:13.179 --> 05:14.612
[ Screams ]

05:14.647 --> 05:16.448
[ Screaming ]

05:16.483 --> 05:17.482
Ow.

05:17.517 --> 05:19.384
[ Groaning ]

05:19.419 --> 05:21.019
[ Chuckles ]
All good!

05:21.054 --> 05:22.053
Cool, man.

05:22.088 --> 05:23.722
Now use this cane
to keep off it.

05:23.757 --> 05:25.457
You should be fine.

05:25.492 --> 05:28.293
Why don't we let Grizz
hold this?

05:28.328 --> 05:29.561
So, can we go now?

05:29.596 --> 05:31.963
Almost. Just got to test
your blood sample.

05:31.998 --> 05:33.131
It'll only be a sec.

05:33.166 --> 05:35.233
Huh.

05:35.268 --> 05:38.670
I'll...be right back.

05:38.705 --> 05:41.339
Stay put, now.

05:41.374 --> 05:42.841
That seemed
a little weird.

05:42.876 --> 05:44.008
Uh, fellas?

05:44.043 --> 05:45.310
I'm getting the ol'
heebie-jeebies here.

05:45.345 --> 05:46.644
I think we should
skedaddle.

05:46.679 --> 05:48.380
Shouldn't we wait
for the results?

05:48.415 --> 05:49.881
No, no, I got to get
out of here.

05:49.916 --> 05:51.583
He knows something.
I can feel it in my bones.

05:51.618 --> 05:53.017
[ Knock on door ]
[ Gasps ]

05:53.052 --> 05:55.387
Clear all his surgeries.
This is his top priority.

05:55.422 --> 05:57.522
Quick,
get behind Panda.

05:57.557 --> 05:59.324
Behind me, you dummy!

05:59.359 --> 06:00.558
Oh, right.
Right.

06:00.593 --> 06:02.160
Okay, just look normal.

06:02.195 --> 06:03.495
[ Clears throat ]
Okay.

06:03.530 --> 06:05.397
Good news is your test results
are done.

06:05.432 --> 06:08.933
The bad news is that literally
everything is wrong with you.

06:08.968 --> 06:10.402
We need to operate
to find out more.

06:10.437 --> 06:11.903
-Come get him, guys!
-Wait, what?

06:11.938 --> 06:13.671
-Okay, uh, what's going on?
-Stop.

06:13.706 --> 06:15.874
-No! No, let go of me!
-Panda! Hey, Panda!

06:15.909 --> 06:17.776
Hold it. Never seen
these results before.

06:17.811 --> 06:19.944
We need to find out
if he's contagious to others.

06:19.979 --> 06:21.679
Plus, he signed
this consent form.

06:21.714 --> 06:23.615
Trust me, it's for your
brother's own good.

06:23.650 --> 06:24.883
If you try to interfere,

06:24.918 --> 06:26.418
I'm going to have
to call security.

06:26.453 --> 06:27.952
Doctor, wait! No!

06:27.987 --> 06:29.187
[ Groans ]

06:29.222 --> 06:30.221
Despair.

06:30.256 --> 06:31.689
What'd I miss?

06:31.724 --> 06:33.057
No, let me go!

06:33.092 --> 06:36.528
W-Why am I strapped down?!
What is going on?!

06:36.563 --> 06:37.695
Hey, Panda.

06:37.730 --> 06:39.063
Dr. Clark,
what is happening?!

06:39.098 --> 06:41.232
We're taking you in
for surgery right now.

06:41.267 --> 06:43.401
But I don't need surgery!
I'm fine.

06:43.436 --> 06:45.303
See?
[ Laughs ]

06:45.338 --> 06:46.938
Yeah, he's delirious.
Take him to op room 3.

06:46.973 --> 06:48.640
No, no, no, no, no!
I'm fine! Just let me go!

06:48.675 --> 06:50.408
I'll send for the specialist
surgeon right away.

06:50.443 --> 06:51.376
Yes, sir.

06:51.411 --> 06:53.478
I don't need surgery!

06:58.017 --> 06:59.784
So this is
- the strange patient, huh?

06:59.819 --> 07:02.153
He doesn't look so strange.
He just looks like a panda.

07:02.188 --> 07:03.955
Yeah, but I heard
he has blue blood.

07:03.990 --> 07:05.423
Panda:
You guys are crazy!

07:05.458 --> 07:06.658
Let me go!
Please, help me!

07:06.693 --> 07:07.725
-Help! Help!
-Quick, hold him down!

07:07.760 --> 07:08.893
No, let me go!

07:08.928 --> 07:10.962
This is all Charlie's fault!

07:10.997 --> 07:12.931
He's too hysterical!
Get the gas!

07:12.966 --> 07:13.998
Gas?!

07:14.033 --> 07:16.935
Grizz:
Ohh, what are we going to do?!

07:16.970 --> 07:18.736
I heard they have
a specialist surgeon.

07:18.771 --> 07:20.238
He could be surgering him
right now!

07:20.273 --> 07:22.774
This is my fault.
Me and my dumb foot.

07:22.809 --> 07:24.609
Now my Pan Pan's
in danger.

07:24.644 --> 07:26.277
[ Sobs ]

07:26.312 --> 07:27.612
Don't give up, Charlie.

07:27.647 --> 07:28.980
We're going to figure
something out, man.

07:29.015 --> 07:30.448
Think, Grizz,
think, Grizz, think, Grizz.

07:30.483 --> 07:32.784
Ice Bear: All of Ice Bear's
ideas involve fireworks.

07:32.819 --> 07:35.920
Blimp, catapult, bandages.

07:35.955 --> 07:36.921
Ah.

07:36.956 --> 07:37.822
Oh.

07:37.857 --> 07:39.791
Guys, I think
I have a bad idea.

07:39.826 --> 07:41.092
What kind of bad idea?

07:41.127 --> 07:43.461
Ice Bear would prefer
a good idea.

07:43.496 --> 07:44.496
Oh, yeah.

07:44.531 --> 07:46.297
Ahh! No! No!
I don't want it!

07:46.332 --> 07:48.266
[ Gas hissing ] Sir, calm down.
This will help.

07:48.301 --> 07:49.667
No! Get away!

07:49.702 --> 07:50.969
Gotcha!

07:51.004 --> 07:54.672
That's it, big guy.
Take deep breaths.

07:54.707 --> 07:56.274
[ Laughing ]

07:56.309 --> 07:57.642
Charlie: Ahem!

07:57.677 --> 07:59.177
Who are you?

08:02.682 --> 08:06.150
Hello.
I am Doctor, uh, Castle,

08:06.185 --> 08:08.019
and these
are my trusty nurses,

08:08.054 --> 08:10.488
Nurse, uh, Swords
and Nurse --

08:10.523 --> 08:12.824
shoot -- uh, Grizz,
Nurse Grizz.

08:12.859 --> 08:14.659
Oh, you must be
the specialty surgeon?

08:14.694 --> 08:18.162
[ Laughing ]
You're a surgeon!

08:18.197 --> 08:19.464
A surgeon!

08:19.499 --> 08:20.865
I think
that's enough gas.

08:20.900 --> 08:25.169
Aha, so this is the patient
I've heard to much about.

08:25.204 --> 08:26.471
[ Laughing ]

08:26.506 --> 08:27.672
Oh!

08:27.707 --> 08:30.642
♪♪

08:30.677 --> 08:33.745
Oh, hey, guys!
Look, I know them!

08:33.780 --> 08:36.080
Oh, you're so beautiful!

08:36.115 --> 08:37.015
Nurses?

08:37.050 --> 08:38.883
Uhp, we'll handle it
from here.

08:38.918 --> 08:40.752
Why are you dressed like --

08:40.787 --> 08:42.253
Thank you
- for what you've done so far.

08:42.288 --> 08:43.988
-We are professionals.
-Oh, Dr. Castle?

08:44.023 --> 08:45.657
Yes, just tell us
what we need to do.

08:45.692 --> 08:47.158
So what procedures
are you going to do?

08:47.193 --> 08:48.726
I can't wait to see
your technique.

08:48.761 --> 08:50.228
Please, please,
so excited to be here.

08:50.263 --> 08:52.363
Can we help?
- Do -- Do you need anything?

08:52.398 --> 08:53.698
Uh, you could...

08:53.733 --> 08:55.199
close your eyes.

08:55.234 --> 08:56.701
Um, why, sir?

08:56.736 --> 09:00.238
Because I want you to, um,

09:00.273 --> 09:03.241
visualize the surgery.

09:03.276 --> 09:04.509
Oh, wow, wow.
- Oh!

09:04.544 --> 09:07.712
It must be a brand-new technique.
- Of course.

09:07.747 --> 09:09.180
We are ready to learn.

09:09.215 --> 09:12.350
Charlie: Great.
Now take a step to your right.

09:12.385 --> 09:13.251
Bit more.

09:13.286 --> 09:14.519
Tiny bit more.

09:14.554 --> 09:16.054
Perfect!

09:16.089 --> 09:19.257
Now keep 'em closed.
I will begin the surgery stuff.

09:19.292 --> 09:21.426
[ Wheels squeaking ]

09:21.461 --> 09:24.128
I can hear
the cutting.

09:24.163 --> 09:26.264
[ Sighing ]

09:26.299 --> 09:27.398
Wait.

09:27.433 --> 09:28.566
What was that sound?

09:28.601 --> 09:31.269
Oh, that was his,
um, spleen!

09:31.304 --> 09:33.071
Oh!      Oh!      Oh!

09:33.106 --> 09:33.972
Yeah.

09:34.007 --> 09:37.241
I'm a spleen!
I'm a spleen!

09:37.276 --> 09:38.376
[ Muffled grunting ]

09:38.411 --> 09:40.645
What was ---
Oh, he's stealing a patient!

09:40.680 --> 09:41.613
Ah!

09:41.648 --> 09:43.648
Vamanos, muchachos!

09:45.318 --> 09:46.384
[ Gasps ]

09:46.419 --> 09:48.219
[ Alarm sounding ]

09:48.254 --> 09:49.420
[ Laughs ] Yow!

09:49.455 --> 09:51.422
They're gaining on us!
We need to go faster!

09:51.457 --> 09:52.423
Get on!

09:52.458 --> 09:53.458
Yeah!

09:53.493 --> 09:54.592
Don't let them
get away!

09:54.627 --> 09:55.760
Aah!

09:55.795 --> 09:58.229
[ Babbling ]

09:58.264 --> 09:59.330
Doing okay, Panda?

09:59.365 --> 10:02.333
I'm doing amazing!
I can see everything!

10:02.368 --> 10:04.102
♪♪

10:04.137 --> 10:06.070
I'm afraid
you'll never dance again.

10:06.105 --> 10:07.805
Doctor:
Don't let them get away!

10:07.840 --> 10:09.507
Come on!
We got to catch 'em!

10:09.542 --> 10:11.342
Hey, I know them.

10:11.377 --> 10:12.677
Make a left, Charlie!

10:12.712 --> 10:14.145
[ Glass shatters ]
Oh, sorry!

10:14.180 --> 10:14.946
Whee!

10:14.981 --> 10:16.781
Stop 'em!
Close the doors!

10:16.816 --> 10:18.316
Yes, sir!

10:19.652 --> 10:21.152
[ Laughing ] Oh!

10:21.187 --> 10:22.754
We're stuck!

10:22.789 --> 10:23.955
Okay,
we got to go, guys!

10:23.990 --> 10:25.256
Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!
Move it, guys!

10:25.291 --> 10:27.458
♪ We got stuck,
we got stuck ♪

10:27.493 --> 10:28.693
Stop right there!

10:28.728 --> 10:29.827
Get back here!

10:29.862 --> 10:32.163
Oh, man,
we are so fired.

10:33.332 --> 10:35.633
Charlie: Ah, guys, thanks
for getting my foot fixed.

10:35.668 --> 10:37.135
It feels better
than ever.

10:37.170 --> 10:39.937
Ah, it was nothing, Charlie.
That's what friends are for.

10:39.972 --> 10:42.140
Now who wants to finish
"Swords and Castles"?

10:42.175 --> 10:43.808
Ice Bear needs
his drama fix.

10:43.843 --> 10:44.942
[ Static hisses ]

10:44.977 --> 10:46.678
Oh, right,
the satellite's out.

10:46.713 --> 10:47.845
